# REST Client Test File for Contact Management System API
# Install the "REST Client" extension in VS Code to send these requests directly from this file.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000

### 1. Check Server and Database Status
GET {{baseUrl}}/status

###

### 2. Create Contact 1 (John Doe) - Success Case
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/contacts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "phone": "+1234567890",
  "address": "123 Main St",
  "company": "ACME Inc"
}

###

### 3. Create Contact 2 (Alice Smith) - Success Case
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/contacts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Alice Smith",
  "email": "alice@company.com",
  "phone": "+1122334455",
  "address": "456 Elm St",
  "company": "Beta Corp"
}

###

### 4. Create Contact with Duplicate Email (Expected: 400 Bad Request)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/contacts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Duplicate",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "phone": "+9876543210",
  "address": "321 Second St",
  "company": "ACME Copied"
}

###

### 5. Create Contact with Invalid Email & Phone (Expected: 400 Bad Request)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/contacts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "",
  "email": "not-an-email",
  "phone": "123"
}

###

### 6. Get All Contacts (Supports search, pagination, and sorting)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/contacts?page=1&limit=5&sortBy=name&order=asc

###

### 7. Search Contacts (Partial match on name, email, or phone)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/contacts?search=Alice

###

### 8. Get Single Contact by ID
# NOTE: Replace the ID below with a valid MongoDB ID returned from a previous POST request.
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/contacts/64b0f9f3c1d9b3d0a2f4a56a

###

### 9. Update Contact by ID (Success Case)
# NOTE: Replace the ID below with a valid MongoDB ID.
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/contacts/64b0f9f3c1d9b3d0a2f4a56a
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe Updated",
  "email": "john.updated@example.com",
  "phone": "+1234567890",
  "address": "789 Oak Ave",
  "company": "ACME Corp"
}

###

### 10. Update Contact with a Taken Email (Expected: 400 Bad Request)
# NOTE: Replace the ID below with a valid MongoDB ID (e.g. John's ID).
# We attempt to set John's email to 'alice@company.com' which is already taken by Alice.
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/contacts/64b0f9f3c1d9b3d0a2f4a56a
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "alice@company.com",
  "phone": "+1234567890"
}

###

### 11. Delete Contact by ID
# NOTE: Replace the ID below with a valid MongoDB ID.
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/contacts/64b0f9f3c1d9b3d0a2f4a56a
